# Best Practices for Introducing AI to your class.

#### LLMs are powerful tools, but they shouldn't replace critical thinking and deep understanding in the classroom. By integrating these best practices, you can leverage the benefits of LLMs while fostering valuable learning experiences for your students.


<table border="1" width="800" style="font-size: 16px;"> <!-- Defines a border for clarity and a total width -->
  <col width="300"> <!-- Approximates the left column as narrower -->
  <col width="500"> <!-- Approximates the right column as wider -->
  <tr>
     <td style="background-color: #8de9ef; font-size: 16px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;"><b>Introduce LLMs Responsibly</b></td>
    <td style= "font-size: 15px;  padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;">Briefly discuss how LLMs work and their limitations.

</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color: #dba9f2; font-size: 16px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;padding-left: 5px;"><b>Provide Scaffolded Support</b></td>
    <td style= "font-size: 15px;padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;">Gradually introduce LLMs into classroom activities, providing scaffolded support and guidance as students learn to effectively integrate them into their workflow.
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color: #fcaeae; font-size: 16px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;"><b>Focus on Collaboration</b></td>
    <td style= "font-size: 15px;padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;">Frame LLM use as a tool to enhance students' own skills, not replace them.
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color: #f9b668; font-size: 16px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;"><b>Embrace Exploration </b></td>
    <td style= "font-size: 15px;padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;">Encourage experimentation with LLMs while promoting responsible use.

</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td style="background-color: #8de9ef; font-size: 16px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;"><b>Monitor and Assess</b></td>
    <td style= "font-size: 15px; padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px;"> Regularly monitor student use of LLMs during class activities and assignments. Provide feedback on their use of LLMs, including whether they are using them appropriately and effectively.
</td>
  </tr>
</table>

MARKDOWN
